OL,3,CMother's fear for her future as
OL,4,Cresidency rules set to double
OL,6,FUnder the rules when she arrived, she
OL,7,Fwas eligible to apply for Indefinite
OL,8,FLeave to Remain (ILR) after five years
OL,9,Fof living and working in the country.
OL,11,FHowever, a new government consultation
OL,12,Fproposes extending that qualifying
OL,13,Fperiod to ten years.
OL,15,FFor Petra, who has spent the last
OL,16,Fthree years building a life in Witney,
OL,17,Fthe proposed changes feel like a
OL,18,Fbetrayal of the agreement she signed
OL,19,Fup for.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/7
