OL,3,CMother's fear for her future as
OL,4,Cresidency rules set to double
OL,6,FThe Home Office defended the
OL,7,Fproposals, stating that the reforms
OL,8,Fare necessary to fix what they
OL,9,Fdescribe as a "broken" immigration
OL,10,Fsystem.
OL,12,FA spokesperson said: "TheHome
OL,13,FSecretary has set out her plans for
OL,14,Fthe biggest legal migration reforms in
OL,15,F50 years.
OL,17,F"It is a privilege, not a right, to
OL,18,Fsettle in the UK and it must be
OL,19,Fearned. We are reforming a broken
OL,20,Fimmigration system to prioritise
OL,21,Fcontribution and integration."
